==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|tortuse|lang=enm}}, {{term|tortuce|lang=enm}}, {{term|tortuge|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term|tortuca|lang=la}}, possibly from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|tartarucha|tartarūcha|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|tartaruchus|tartarūchus|of Tartarus|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ταρταροῦχος|tr=tartarouchos||lang=grc|from Tartaros, Tartarus, the land of the dead in ancient stories}}, because it used to be thought that tortoises and turtles came from the underworld; or from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|tortus||lang=la|twisted}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-tortoise.ogg|Audio (US)}}

*: {{rhymes|ɔː(r)təs}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of various land-dwelling [[reptile]]s, of [[family]] ''[[Testudinidae]]'', whose body is enclosed in a [[shell]] ([[carapace]] plus [[plastron]]). The animal can [[withdraw]] its head and four legs partially into the shell, providing some [[protection]] from [[predator]]s.

